#: ../../effects_and_compositions/subtitles.rst:103
msgid "Subtitle window"
msgstr ""

#: ../../effects_and_compositions/subtitles.rst:108
msgid ""
"The subtitles window allows easier editing and also makes it possible to "
"easily navigate between subtitles with the :guilabel:`<` and :guilabel:`>` "
"buttons"
msgstr ""

#: ../../effects_and_compositions/subtitles.rst:110
msgid "With the :guilabel:`+` button you can add subtitles"
msgstr ""

#: ../../effects_and_compositions/subtitles.rst:112
msgid ""
"The scissors are mostly here for dividing subtitles: let's say your subtitle "
"text is too long and you want to make it two different subtitles. Put the "
"cursor in the text widget where you want to cut and click the scissors, it "
"will split the text between two different subtitle items. The scissors are "
"only working when the playhead is over the subtitle itself."
msgstr ""

#: ../../effects_and_compositions/subtitles.rst:114
msgid "The check-mark button adds the text to the subtitle"
msgstr ""

#: ../../effects_and_compositions/subtitles.rst:119
msgid "Character count and zoom"
msgstr ""

#: ../../effects_and_compositions/subtitles.rst:126
msgid ":guilabel:`Character:`: Character number at cursor position"
msgstr ""

#: ../../effects_and_compositions/subtitles.rst:128
msgid ":guilabel:`total:`: Total number of Character"
msgstr ""

